From c81a723f5ffac06b9956f0fe5989791e4650445f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ingo Molnar <mingo@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 17 Mar 2025 11:42:54 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] sched/debug: Make CONFIG_SCHED_DEBUG functionality
 unconditional

References: bsc#1234634 (Scheduler functional and performance backports SL-16.1)
Patch-mainline: v6.15-rc1
Git-commit: dd5bdaf2b72da81d57f4f99e518af80002b6562e

All the big Linux distros enable CONFIG_SCHED_DEBUG, because
the various features it provides help not just with kernel
development, but with system administration and user-space
software development as well.

Reflect this reality and enable this functionality
unconditionally.

Signed-off-by: Ingo Molnar <mingo@kernel.org>
